Message.message: "A beautiful ring!"
Found my precious Tiara!
It's a disgrace! Torn to pieces...
Got my Tiara, but the wolf is chasing me!
My Tiara may be in pieces... but I won't!
You found my Tiara! Thank you!
You found my Tiara... smashed?! Better than nothing.
Forget the perfect Tiara, wolves are chasing us!
Since you failed to protect the Tiara could you at least protect me from the wolves?
Now we're safe... aren't we?
Now we're safe... aren't we?
Finaly, we're all safe. Except my  broken Tiara...
Finaly, we're all safe. Except my  broken Tiara...
You found my father's stashed sword!
Wolves won't dare biting a swordholder.
Wait... have you never held a sword before?
You can practise with those crates.
Just let your in-x-tinct guide you!
This is no time for a swim!
Hot! Hot! Ouch!
Only six more to go!
Still five Tiaras remaining!
Four Tiaras yet to be found!
Three last Tiaras to discover!
Just two more Tiaras and I'll be happy!
Let's get the final Tiara. I can't wait!
Finally, we've gathered all Tiaras!!
Oh? Is my Tiara across the river?
Will you fetch it for me?
This trail of empty crates and scattered treasure was left behind...
... by bandits who sneaked into our palace under the cover of the night.
They subdued my guards and locked us in the tower...
... started packing and removing our assets,...
... when my father, the King, arrived earlier from an overseas expedition.
He was so irate even I was scared!
Those burglars even dared to use our own torches...
...to illuminate their traffic across the river...
... which they hastily abandoned, chased by our troops.
The cowards disbanded as soon as they saw a glimpse of my father's sword!
You too, should be brave like my father!
The thieves intended to sell our treasure to the neighboring kings...
... who always envied the rich bounties of our expeditions.
I could see that in their eyes at our exuberant palace parties.
So I suspect they helped finance the whole shipping operation:
... dozens of boats crammed on this temporary floating platform.
"Never trust other Kings!" - my father said.
I trusted you because you're not a King. Go on!
I'm afraid wolves will attack us unless we do something clever.
Don't ask me what, you are the hero!
Do something!
Not all mercenaries came by boat...
... and many were left by their fleeing peers in this dense forest.
Obviously they didn't carry their cargo far deep into the woods...
... and the little they carried would have been dropped under a wolf attack.
Let us hope they left behind any Tiara!
Wolves are chasing us again!
Get rid of them!
From an early age, my father taught me how to use his sword...
... so I could defend myself when he was away.
That night, after scaring away the crooks,...
... he was so displeased to see me and the guards subdued...
... that he sent me on a quest to recover the seven Tiaras...
... which had belonged to our dinasty for generations.
Then he forbade everyone in the Kingdom from helping me!
So lucky to have found a foreigner like you!
I can't bear any more wolves!
It doesn't matter that you've got a sword, I am unarmed...
... and will burn this bridge if I have to!
I'll never become a Queen...
... unless I can complete this Quest.
My father threatened to abdicate...
... in favour of an elected government!
Don't you even pretend to entertain the idea!
(sigh) Please!
I'll manage the sword, you use your head!
What kind of hero are you? Protect me!
Our quest is over! We recovered...
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 7 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Perfect! ~
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 6 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Excellent! ~
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 5 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Impressive! ~
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 4 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Great! ~
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 3 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Nice!
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 2 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Not bad! ~
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 1 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Good effort! ~
~ ~ ~ Intact Tiaras: 0 of 7 ~ ~ ~    ~ Actually not that easy! ~
Let's return to the palace!
What? A special gift for me?
Oh! Such a magnificient ring!
My father will absolutely approve of us...
My father will reward your bravery ...
... and our sucess story shall be sung forever in our Kingdom. We'll name it the legend of...
Hand me your sword now. It is too dangerous for you.
Be careful with your sword! Last warning.
Hey! You almost cut my expensive dress with your clumsy swordmanship!
Wait! Maybe you could help me...
... recover the others?
Let's cross the river. You go first!
Look there! A stolen torch, still burning.
Don't let it too close to the trees, you may start a fire.
A dangerous crate bridge...
... and a rather heavy boulder?
You go ahead! I'll stay and coordinate.
Finally, we've crossed the river!
Now we must venture deep into the forest to reach the kingdom's frontier.
Did you hear that howl?
Wolves must not be far from us.
No, I'm not hiding!
I'm looking for a sword my father stashed somewhere.
This is the last Tiara!
I'll stay here by this torch.
Call me if you need help!
Wait for me please!
Bad wolf! Help! I'm fainting...
Look out! Are you OK?
Ouch! Tiaras are so fragile!
Don't leave me alone with the wolf!
My precious Tiara (sigh)...
... forever lost!
